<reference id="External-Breed-Reference">
  <title>External Breed Reference: Boxer–Australian Shepherd</title>
  <shortdesc>
    Learn more about the Boxer and Australian Shepherd breeds. 
    These external links provide detailed information about the breeds’ temperament, energy levels, and care needs.
  </shortdesc>

  <refbody>
    <section>
      <title>Boxer Breed Information</title>
      <p>
        For an overview of the Boxer breed, including health, exercise, and personality traits, 
        visit the American Kennel Club (AKC) Boxer breed page:
      </p>
      <p>
        <xref format="html" href="https://www.akc.org/dog-breeds/boxer/">Boxer Breed Info (AKC)</xref>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Australian Shepherd Breed Information</title>
      <p>
        For an overview of the Australian Shepherd breed, including care, socialization, and training needs, 
        visit the American Kennel Club (AKC) Australian Shepherd breed page:
      </p>
      <p>
        <xref format="html" href="https://www.akc.org/dog-breeds/australian-shepherd/">Australian Shepherd Breed Info (AKC)</xref>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Why This Matters for Cerberus</title>
      <p>
        Cerberus is a Boxer–Australian Shepherd mix. 
        Understanding these breeds’ general characteristics can help adopters 
        prepare for his high energy, intelligence, and need for structured activity. 
        Individual personality and history will vary, so use this as general context only.
      </p>
    </section>
